{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KHgqaLUPdKvXjiDKih7urg","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary report.\n\n## Agent Triggers System - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Contract File: `docs/agent-triggers-contract.md`\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/agent-triggers-contract.md`\n\nThe contract file fully documents the Rust implementation of the agent triggers system with:\n\n- **Objective:** Define contracts for local scheduler (AGENT_TRIGGERS) and remote trigger dispatch (AGENT_TRIGGERS_REMOTE) with explicit ownership, durability, and authorization behavior\n- **Evidence references:** Points to TypeScript implementation in tools.ts and skills registry\n- **Rust Boundary Mapping:** Spans 7 crates (api-types, app-services, tool-runtime, state-store, remote-runtime, config, and UI)\n- **Core Contracts:** Defines TriggerScope enum, TriggerOwner enum, TriggerTask struct, and two async traits (TriggerSchedulerService, RemoteTriggerDispatchService)\n- **Error Taxonomy:** 7 error types documented\n- **Policy Rules:** 4 rules covering durable task restrictions, ownership checks, and remote dispatch requirements\n- **Acceptance Matrix:** 3 categories of tests (contract, integration, CLI behavior)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Crate Structure\n\nThe system is organized across the workspace as follows:\n\n| Crate | Purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `crates/application` | Contains spec_contracts.rs with type definitions and trait interfaces |\n| `crates/platform` | Implements trigger services (LocalTriggerSchedulerService, PlatformRemoteTriggerDispatchService) |\n| `crates/state-store` | Handles durable task persistence (FileTriggerTaskStateStore) |\n| `crates/cron` | Validates cron expressions |\n| `crates/remote-runtime` | Provides AuthContext and AuthContextProvider for remote dispatch |\n| `crates/domain` | Provides core domain types like SessionId and DomainEvent |\n\n---\n\n### 3. Core Types and Enums\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/spec_contracts.rs` (lines 121-172)\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub enum TriggerScope {\n    SessionOnly,     // Task survives runtime but not process restart\n    Durable,         // Task persists across process restarts\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub enum TriggerOwner {\n    MainAgent,\n    Teammate(String),\n    TeamLead,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct TriggerTask {\n    pub id: String,\n    pub cron: String,\n    pub prompt: String,\n    pub scope: TriggerScope,\n    pub owner: TriggerOwner,\n    pub durable_intent: bool,  // Required for durable scope\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, thiserror::Error)]\npub enum TriggerError {\n    #[error(\"gate disabled\")]\n    GateDisabled,\n    #[error(\"invalid cron\")]\n    InvalidCron,\n    #[error(\"ownership violation\")]\n    OwnershipViolation,\n    #[error(\"durable tasks not allowed for teammates\")]\n    DurableNotAllowedForTeammate,\n    #[error(\"unauthorized\")]\n    Unauthorized,\n    #[error(\"upstream remote error\")]\n    UpstreamRemoteError,\n    #[error(\"storage error\")]\n    StorageError,\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Core Service Traits\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/spec_contracts.rs` (lines 162-172)\n\n```rust\n#[async_trait]\npub trait TriggerSchedulerService: Send + Sync {\n    async fn create(&self, task: TriggerTask) -> Result<TriggerTask, TriggerError>;\n    async fn list(&self) -> Result<Vec<TriggerTask>, TriggerError>;\n    async fn delete(&self, id: &str, actor: TriggerOwner) -> Result<(), TriggerError>;\n}\n\n#[async_trait]\npub trait RemoteTriggerDispatchService: Send + Sync {\n    async fn dispatch(&self, payload: serde_json::Value) -> Result<String, TriggerError>;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Implementation: LocalTriggerSchedulerService\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/trigger_scheduler_service.rs`\n\nThe service implements comprehensive validation:\n\n- **enable_enabled():** Checks scheduler_enabled policy\n- **validate_create():** Enforces\n  - Valid cron syntax (via ccode_cron crate)\n  - Durable scope requires both durable_intent=true AND durable_enabled policy\n  - Teammates cannot create durable tasks (DurableNotAllowedForTeammate error)\n  \n- **create():** Saves to durable store if scope==Durable, always keeps in-memory\n- **list():** Returns sorted task list (gate-protected)\n- **delete():** Validates owner identity before removal, deletes from durable store if needed\n\n---\n\n### 6. Implementation: PlatformRemoteTriggerDispatchService\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/remote_trigger_dispatch_service.rs`\n\nThe service orchestrates remote dispatch:\n\n- **ensure_enabled():** Checks remote_dispatch_enabled policy → GateDisabled\n- **validated_auth_context():** Validates token and org_id are both present → Unauthorized\n- **dispatch():** Executes transport with auth, maps transport errors to UpstreamRemoteError (non-leaky)\n\nUses trait abstraction for transport layer:\n```rust\n#[async_trait]\npub trait RemoteTriggerTransport: Send + Sync {\n    async fn dispatch(&self, payload: Value, auth: &AuthContext) -> Result<String, String>;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. Persistence Layer\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/state-store/src/lib.rs`\n\n```rust\npub struct FileTriggerTaskStateStore {\n    dir: PathBuf,  // Defaults to {root}/trigger-tasks/\n}\n\n#[async_trait]\npub trait TriggerTaskStateStore: Send + Sync {\n    async fn load_trigger_tasks(&self) -> Result<Vec<Value>, StateStoreError>;\n    async fn save_trigger_task(&self, id: &str, task: &Value) -> Result<(), StateStoreError>;\n    async fn delete_trigger_task(&self, id: &str) -> Result<(), StateStoreError>;\n}\n```\n\n**Storage mechanics:**\n- Each task saved as `{id}.json` in trigger-tasks directory\n- Atomic write using `.tmp` file with rename\n- Corrupt files logged as warnings and skipped\n- Tasks sorted by ID on load\n\n---\n\n### 8. Acceptance Test Pattern\n\n**File examined:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/kairos_acceptance_tests.rs` (698 lines)\n\nThe test pattern follows three-tier organization (matching contract spec):\n\n**§7.1 Contract Tests - Determinism & Error Contracts**\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn contract_mode_resolution_is_deterministic_for_same_inputs() {\n    // Verify same inputs always produce same outputs\n    // Test for each variant of error paths\n}\n```\n\n**§7.2 Integration Tests - End-to-End Scenarios**\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn integration_brief_mode_filters_brief_blocked_tools() {\n    // Multi-step scenarios with real policy interaction\n}\n```\n\n**§7.3 CLI Behaviour Tests - User-Facing Semantics**\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn cli_assistant_mode_entry_session_overrides_config() {\n    // Test session/config precedence and side effects\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. Trigger System Unit Tests\n\n**Trigger Scheduler Tests:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/trigger_scheduler_service_tests.rs` (255 lines)\n\nTest coverage includes:\n\n1. **Durability contract:**\n   - `durable_persists_and_reloads_on_restart()` - Durable tasks survive restart\n   - `session_only_survives_runtime_but_not_restart()` - Session tasks don't persist\n\n2. **Ownership enforcement:**\n   - `teammate_cannot_create_durable()` - Returns DurableNotAllowedForTeammate\n   - `delete_checks_owner_identity()` - Owner mismatch returns OwnershipViolation\n\n3. **Validation:**\n   - `invalid_cron_returns_invalid_cron_error()` - Cron syntax checking\n   - `durable_requires_explicit_user_intent()` - durable_intent flag required\n\n4. **Policy gates:**\n   - `gate_disabled_returns_gate_disabled()` - Feature gate enforcement\n   - `storage_error_is_mapped_from_store_failures()` - Error mapping\n\n**Remote Dispatch Tests:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/remote_trigger_dispatch_service_tests.rs` (205 lines)\n\nTest coverage includes:\n\n1. **Gate protection:**\n   - `gate_off_returns_gate_disabled()` - Remote dispatch disabled\n\n2. **Authentication:**\n   - `missing_auth_or_org_returns_unauthorized()` - Token and org validation\n\n3. **Error handling:**\n   - `transport_errors_map_to_non_leaky_upstream_remote_error()` - Details not leaked\n\n4. **Independence:**\n   - `local_scheduler_still_works_when_remote_dispatch_is_disabled()` - Services decouple\n\n---\n\n### 10. Test Patterns Used\n\nBoth trigger test suites follow this structure:\n\n```rust\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn scenario_name() {\n    // Setup: Use unique_temp_dir() for isolated test stores\n    let dir = unique_temp_dir(\"scenario-label\");\n    let store = Arc::new(FileTriggerTaskStateStore::new(&dir).expect(\"store\"));\n    \n    // Create service with default or customized policy\n    let service = LocalTriggerSchedulerService::new(store, TriggerSchedulerPolicy::default())\n        .await\n        .expect(\"service\");\n    \n    // Execute and assert error type\n    let err = service.operation().await.expect_err(\"reason\");\n    assert!(matches!(err, TriggerError::ExpectedVariant));\n}\n```\n\nHelper functions:\n- `unique_temp_dir(label)` - Creates timestamped temp directory per test\n- `task(id, scope, owner)` - Constructs test TriggerTask with valid defaults\n- Mock impls of `AuthContextProvider` and `RemoteTriggerTransport` for testability\n\n---\n\n### 11. Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Policy-Driven Behavior:** All services accept policy structs (TriggerSchedulerPolicy, RemoteTriggerDispatchPolicy) enabling feature gates\n2. **Error Taxonomy:** 7 distinct error types map to specific user-facing messages\n3. **Ownership Semantics:** TriggerOwner enum enforces multi-tenant constraints\n4. **Scope Semantics:** TriggerScope determines storage behavior (memory-only vs durable)\n5. **Non-Leaky Errors:** UpstreamRemoteError masks transport details\n6. **Trait Abstraction:** RemoteTriggerTransport allows for mock/test implementations\n7. **Atomic Persistence:** File-based store uses .tmp rename pattern\n\n---\n\n### 12. File Paths Summary\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/agent-triggers-contract.md` | Contract specification |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/spec_contracts.rs` | Core type definitions and traits |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/trigger_scheduler_service.rs` | Local scheduler implementation |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/trigger_scheduler_service_tests.rs` | Scheduler unit tests |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/remote_trigger_dispatch_service.rs` | Remote dispatch implementation |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/remote_trigger_dispatch_service_tests.rs` | Remote dispatch unit tests |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/state-store/src/lib.rs` | Durable persistence layer |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/kairos_acceptance_tests.rs` | Acceptance test pattern reference |"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f364ad52-4738-45a7-8cb7-9f4703f698a1","uuid":"a888c8a9-2327-49f3-bf16-42c410cc4155","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:47:12.374Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the agent triggers system in this Rust codebase. Find:\n\n1. The file `agent-triggers-contract.md` - read its full contents\n2. Any existing acceptance test files (look in `tests/` directories, especially patterns like `*acceptance*`, `*triggers*`, `*agent*`)\n3. The crate structure - what crates exist and which one handles triggers\n4. Any existing trigger-related source code (types, enums like DurableNotAllowedForTeammate, InvalidCron, OwnershipViolation, GateDisabled, etc.)\n5. Look at a recent acceptance test file (e.g., US-043 or US-042) for the test pattern used\n\nBe very thorough - read the contract file fully and at least one recent test file fully.","agentId":"af416a9ceb6d46e94","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary report.\n\n## Agent Triggers System - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Contract File: `docs/agent-triggers-contract.md`\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/agent-triggers-contract.md`\n\nThe contract file fully documents the Rust implementation of the agent triggers system with:\n\n- **Objective:** Define contracts for local scheduler (AGENT_TRIGGERS) and remote trigger dispatch (AGENT_TRIGGERS_REMOTE) with explicit ownership, durability, and authorization behavior\n- **Evidence references:** Points to TypeScript implementation in tools.ts and skills registry\n- **Rust Boundary Mapping:** Spans 7 crates (api-types, app-services, tool-runtime, state-store, remote-runtime, config, and UI)\n- **Core Contracts:** Defines TriggerScope enum, TriggerOwner enum, TriggerTask struct, and two async traits (TriggerSchedulerService, RemoteTriggerDispatchService)\n- **Error Taxonomy:** 7 error types documented\n- **Policy Rules:** 4 rules covering durable task restrictions, ownership checks, and remote dispatch requirements\n- **Acceptance Matrix:** 3 categories of tests (contract, integration, CLI behavior)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Crate Structure\n\nThe system is organized across the workspace as follows:\n\n| Crate | Purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `crates/application` | Contains spec_contracts.rs with type definitions and trait interfaces |\n| `crates/platform` | Implements trigger services (LocalTriggerSchedulerService, PlatformRemoteTriggerDispatchService) |\n| `crates/state-store` | Handles durable task persistence (FileTriggerTaskStateStore) |\n| `crates/cron` | Validates cron expressions |\n| `crates/remote-runtime` | Provides AuthContext and AuthContextProvider for remote dispatch |\n| `crates/domain` | Provides core domain types like SessionId and DomainEvent |\n\n---\n\n### 3. Core Types and Enums\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/spec_contracts.rs` (lines 121-172)\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub enum TriggerScope {\n    SessionOnly,     // Task survives runtime but not process restart\n    Durable,         // Task persists across process restarts\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub enum TriggerOwner {\n    MainAgent,\n    Teammate(String),\n    TeamLead,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct TriggerTask {\n    pub id: String,\n    pub cron: String,\n    pub prompt: String,\n    pub scope: TriggerScope,\n    pub owner: TriggerOwner,\n    pub durable_intent: bool,  // Required for durable scope\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, thiserror::Error)]\npub enum TriggerError {\n    #[error(\"gate disabled\")]\n    GateDisabled,\n    #[error(\"invalid cron\")]\n    InvalidCron,\n    #[error(\"ownership violation\")]\n    OwnershipViolation,\n    #[error(\"durable tasks not allowed for teammates\")]\n    DurableNotAllowedForTeammate,\n    #[error(\"unauthorized\")]\n    Unauthorized,\n    #[error(\"upstream remote error\")]\n    UpstreamRemoteError,\n    #[error(\"storage error\")]\n    StorageError,\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Core Service Traits\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/spec_contracts.rs` (lines 162-172)\n\n```rust\n#[async_trait]\npub trait TriggerSchedulerService: Send + Sync {\n    async fn create(&self, task: TriggerTask) -> Result<TriggerTask, TriggerError>;\n    async fn list(&self) -> Result<Vec<TriggerTask>, TriggerError>;\n    async fn delete(&self, id: &str, actor: TriggerOwner) -> Result<(), TriggerError>;\n}\n\n#[async_trait]\npub trait RemoteTriggerDispatchService: Send + Sync {\n    async fn dispatch(&self, payload: serde_json::Value) -> Result<String, TriggerError>;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Implementation: LocalTriggerSchedulerService\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/trigger_scheduler_service.rs`\n\nThe service implements comprehensive validation:\n\n- **enable_enabled():** Checks scheduler_enabled policy\n- **validate_create():** Enforces\n  - Valid cron syntax (via ccode_cron crate)\n  - Durable scope requires both durable_intent=true AND durable_enabled policy\n  - Teammates cannot create durable tasks (DurableNotAllowedForTeammate error)\n  \n- **create():** Saves to durable store if scope==Durable, always keeps in-memory\n- **list():** Returns sorted task list (gate-protected)\n- **delete():** Validates owner identity before removal, deletes from durable store if needed\n\n---\n\n### 6. Implementation: PlatformRemoteTriggerDispatchService\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/remote_trigger_dispatch_service.rs`\n\nThe service orchestrates remote dispatch:\n\n- **ensure_enabled():** Checks remote_dispatch_enabled policy → GateDisabled\n- **validated_auth_context():** Validates token and org_id are both present → Unauthorized\n- **dispatch():** Executes transport with auth, maps transport errors to UpstreamRemoteError (non-leaky)\n\nUses trait abstraction for transport layer:\n```rust\n#[async_trait]\npub trait RemoteTriggerTransport: Send + Sync {\n    async fn dispatch(&self, payload: Value, auth: &AuthContext) -> Result<String, String>;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. Persistence Layer\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/state-store/src/lib.rs`\n\n```rust\npub struct FileTriggerTaskStateStore {\n    dir: PathBuf,  // Defaults to {root}/trigger-tasks/\n}\n\n#[async_trait]\npub trait TriggerTaskStateStore: Send + Sync {\n    async fn load_trigger_tasks(&self) -> Result<Vec<Value>, StateStoreError>;\n    async fn save_trigger_task(&self, id: &str, task: &Value) -> Result<(), StateStoreError>;\n    async fn delete_trigger_task(&self, id: &str) -> Result<(), StateStoreError>;\n}\n```\n\n**Storage mechanics:**\n- Each task saved as `{id}.json` in trigger-tasks directory\n- Atomic write using `.tmp` file with rename\n- Corrupt files logged as warnings and skipped\n- Tasks sorted by ID on load\n\n---\n\n### 8. Acceptance Test Pattern\n\n**File examined:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/kairos_acceptance_tests.rs` (698 lines)\n\nThe test pattern follows three-tier organization (matching contract spec):\n\n**§7.1 Contract Tests - Determinism & Error Contracts**\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn contract_mode_resolution_is_deterministic_for_same_inputs() {\n    // Verify same inputs always produce same outputs\n    // Test for each variant of error paths\n}\n```\n\n**§7.2 Integration Tests - End-to-End Scenarios**\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn integration_brief_mode_filters_brief_blocked_tools() {\n    // Multi-step scenarios with real policy interaction\n}\n```\n\n**§7.3 CLI Behaviour Tests - User-Facing Semantics**\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn cli_assistant_mode_entry_session_overrides_config() {\n    // Test session/config precedence and side effects\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. Trigger System Unit Tests\n\n**Trigger Scheduler Tests:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/trigger_scheduler_service_tests.rs` (255 lines)\n\nTest coverage includes:\n\n1. **Durability contract:**\n   - `durable_persists_and_reloads_on_restart()` - Durable tasks survive restart\n   - `session_only_survives_runtime_but_not_restart()` - Session tasks don't persist\n\n2. **Ownership enforcement:**\n   - `teammate_cannot_create_durable()` - Returns DurableNotAllowedForTeammate\n   - `delete_checks_owner_identity()` - Owner mismatch returns OwnershipViolation\n\n3. **Validation:**\n   - `invalid_cron_returns_invalid_cron_error()` - Cron syntax checking\n   - `durable_requires_explicit_user_intent()` - durable_intent flag required\n\n4. **Policy gates:**\n   - `gate_disabled_returns_gate_disabled()` - Feature gate enforcement\n   - `storage_error_is_mapped_from_store_failures()` - Error mapping\n\n**Remote Dispatch Tests:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/remote_trigger_dispatch_service_tests.rs` (205 lines)\n\nTest coverage includes:\n\n1. **Gate protection:**\n   - `gate_off_returns_gate_disabled()` - Remote dispatch disabled\n\n2. **Authentication:**\n   - `missing_auth_or_org_returns_unauthorized()` - Token and org validation\n\n3. **Error handling:**\n   - `transport_errors_map_to_non_leaky_upstream_remote_error()` - Details not leaked\n\n4. **Independence:**\n   - `local_scheduler_still_works_when_remote_dispatch_is_disabled()` - Services decouple\n\n---\n\n### 10. Test Patterns Used\n\nBoth trigger test suites follow this structure:\n\n```rust\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn scenario_name() {\n    // Setup: Use unique_temp_dir() for isolated test stores\n    let dir = unique_temp_dir(\"scenario-label\");\n    let store = Arc::new(FileTriggerTaskStateStore::new(&dir).expect(\"store\"));\n    \n    // Create service with default or customized policy\n    let service = LocalTriggerSchedulerService::new(store, TriggerSchedulerPolicy::default())\n        .await\n        .expect(\"service\");\n    \n    // Execute and assert error type\n    let err = service.operation().await.expect_err(\"reason\");\n    assert!(matches!(err, TriggerError::ExpectedVariant));\n}\n```\n\nHelper functions:\n- `unique_temp_dir(label)` - Creates timestamped temp directory per test\n- `task(id, scope, owner)` - Constructs test TriggerTask with valid defaults\n- Mock impls of `AuthContextProvider` and `RemoteTriggerTransport` for testability\n\n---\n\n### 11. Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Policy-Driven Behavior:** All services accept policy structs (TriggerSchedulerPolicy, RemoteTriggerDispatchPolicy) enabling feature gates\n2. **Error Taxonomy:** 7 distinct error types map to specific user-facing messages\n3. **Ownership Semantics:** TriggerOwner enum enforces multi-tenant constraints\n4. **Scope Semantics:** TriggerScope determines storage behavior (memory-only vs durable)\n5. **Non-Leaky Errors:** UpstreamRemoteError masks transport details\n6. **Trait Abstraction:** RemoteTriggerTransport allows for mock/test implementations\n7. **Atomic Persistence:** File-based store uses .tmp rename pattern\n\n---\n\n### 12. File Paths Summary\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/agent-triggers-contract.md` | Contract specification |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/spec_contracts.rs` | Core type definitions and traits |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/trigger_scheduler_service.rs` | Local scheduler implementation |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/trigger_scheduler_service_tests.rs` | Scheduler unit tests |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/remote_trigger_dispatch_service.rs` | Remote dispatch implementation |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/remote_trigger_dispatch_service_tests.rs` | Remote dispatch unit tests |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/state-store/src/lib.rs` | Durable persistence layer |\n| `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/kairos_acceptance_tests.rs` | Acceptance test pattern reference |"}],"totalDurationMs":50386,"totalTokens":59643,"totalToolUseCount":23,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1356,"cache_read_input_tokens":55002,"output_tokens":3278,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_request