{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AiRYG1vDRk1QA71ELCThYS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# AGENT_TRIGGERS Contract Spec (Rust)\n2\t\n3\t## 1. Objective\n4\t\n5\tDefine Rust contracts for local scheduler (`AGENT_TRIGGERS`) and remote trigger dispatch (`AGENT_TRIGGERS_REMOTE`) with explicit ownership, durability, and authorization behavior.\n6\t\n7\t## 2. Evidence from Current Code\n8\t\n9\t1. `tools.ts:29` (`feature('AGENT_TRIGGERS')`) and cron tools registration.\n10\t2. `tools.ts:36` (`feature('AGENT_TRIGGERS_REMOTE')`) and remote tool registration.\n11\t3. `skills/bundled/index.ts:56` remote scheduling skill registration.\n12\t4. `tools/ScheduleCronTool/CronCreateTool.ts` durable/session-only semantics.\n13\t5. `tools/ScheduleCronTool/CronDeleteTool.ts` ownership constraints.\n14\t6. `utils/cronTasks.ts:1` durable storage at `.claude/scheduled_tasks.json`.\n15\t7. `tools/RemoteTriggerTool/RemoteTriggerTool.ts:59` remote gate (`tengu_surreal_dali`).\n16\t8. `cli/print.ts:2705` scheduler boot path in print/SDK flows.\n17\t\n18\t## 3. Rust Boundary Mapping\n19\t\n20\t1. `crates/api-types`: trigger models, task state, owner scope enums.\n21\t2. `crates/app-services`: scheduling/authorization policy decisions.\n22\t3. `crates/tool-runtime`: trigger tools lifecycle and execution orchestration.\n23\t4. `crates/state-store`: durable task persistence abstraction.\n24\t5. `crates/remote-runtime`: remote trigger API client.\n25\t6. `crates/config`: gate keys, retry/timeouts, file path defaults.\n26\t7. `bins/app-cli` and `crates/ui-tui`: command UX and text output only.\n27\t\n28\t## 4. Core Contracts (Rust Sketch)\n29\t\n30\t```rust\n31\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\n32\tpub enum TriggerScope { SessionOnly, Durable }\n33\t\n34\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\n35\tpub enum TriggerOwner { MainAgent, Teammate(String), TeamLead }\n36\t\n37\t#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n38\tpub struct TriggerTask {\n39\t    pub id: String,\n40\t    pub cron: String,\n41\t    pub prompt: String,\n42\t    pub scope: TriggerScope,\n43\t    pub owner: TriggerOwner,\n44\t    pub recurring: bool,\n45\t}\n46\t\n47\t#[async_trait::async_trait]\n48\tpub trait TriggerSchedulerService {\n49\t    async fn create(&self, task: TriggerTask) -> Result<TriggerTask, TriggerError>;\n50\t    async fn list(&self) -> Result<Vec<TriggerTask>, TriggerError>;\n51\t    async fn delete(&self, id: &str, actor: TriggerOwner) -> Result<(), TriggerError>;\n52\t}\n53\t\n54\t#[async_trait::async_trait]\n55\tpub trait RemoteTriggerDispatchService {\n56\t    async fn dispatch(&self, payload: serde_json::Value) -> Result<String, TriggerError>;\n57\t}\n58\t```\n59\t\n60\t## 5. Error Taxonomy\n61\t\n62\t1. `GateDisabled`\n63\t2. `InvalidCron`\n64\t3. `OwnershipViolation`\n65\t4. `DurableNotAllowedForTeammate`\n66\t5. `Unauthorized`\n67\t6. `UpstreamRemoteError`\n68\t7. `StorageError`\n69\t\n70\t## 6. Policy Rules\n71\t\n72\t1. Durable tasks require explicit user intent.\n73\t2. Teammates cannot create durable tasks.\n74\t3. Delete operation checks owner identity.\n75\t4. Remote dispatch requires both feature gate and auth/org context.\n76\t\n77\t## 7. Constants Classification\n78\t\n79\t1. `api-types`: trigger state labels and protocol field names.\n80\t2. `config`: gate keys (`tengu_kairos_cron`, `tengu_surreal_dali`), path defaults, timeout defaults.\n81\t3. `core-domain`: ownership invariants.\n82\t4. `state-store`/`tool-runtime`: local internal key names and lock file internals.\n83\t5. `ui-tui`: user-facing messages.\n84\t\n85\t## 8. Acceptance Matrix\n86\t\n87\t### Contract tests\n88\t\n89\t1. Durable + teammate returns `DurableNotAllowedForTeammate`.\n90\t2. Invalid cron returns `InvalidCron`.\n91\t3. Owner mismatch delete returns `OwnershipViolation`.\n92\t\n93\t### Integration tests\n94\t\n95\t1. Session-only task survives runtime tick but not process restart.\n96\t2. Durable task reloads from store on restart.\n97\t3. Remote dispatch with gate off returns `GateDisabled`.\n98\t\n99\t### CLI behavior tests\n100\t\n101\t1. List shows scope and owner consistently.\n102\t2. Delete reports deterministic reason on ownership error.\n103\t3. Remote trigger failure prints non-leaky error class.\n104\t\n105\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018v9gKuHTeFVwctEZBEV5Pe","session_id":"f364ad52-4738-45a7-8cb7-9f4703f698a1","uuid":"4cc3036b-9192-43c8-ba38-a551e5bb280e","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:47:20.511Z"}
