{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019kYPKA1qyertfjim65fehH","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t/// KAIROS acceptance tests (US-040)\n2\t///\n3\t/// Covers all scenarios from kairos-contract.md §7 Acceptance Matrix:\n4\t///   §7.1 Contract tests  – mode resolution determinism, route precedence, PromptComposeFailed\n5\t///   §7.2 Integration tests – KAIROS/BRIEF/CHANNELS tool visibility, slash routing, RouteConflict\n6\t///   §7.3 CLI behaviour tests – assistant-mode entry, DisabledByPolicy message, /brief switch\n7\tuse crate::{\n8\t    assistant_mode_service::DefaultAssistantModeService,\n9\t    spec_contracts::{\n10\t        AssistantModeContext, AssistantModeService, CapabilityPolicy, KairosError,\n11\t        PromptComposeContext, PromptPrecedenceLayer, ResolvedModeSource, RouteDecision,\n12\t        RouteInputContext, RouteSource,\n13\t    },\n14\t};\n15\tuse ccode_domain::{\n16\t    assistant_mode::{AssistantMode, ModeSwitchTrigger},\n17\t    event::DomainEvent,\n18\t    session::SessionId,\n19\t};\n20\t\n21\t// ── helpers ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n22\t\n23\tfn sid() -> SessionId {\n24\t    SessionId(\"kairos-test-sess\".into())\n25\t}\n26\t\n27\tfn svc() -> DefaultAssistantModeService {\n28\t    DefaultAssistantModeService\n29\t}\n30\t\n31\tfn default_policy() -> CapabilityPolicy {\n32\t    CapabilityPolicy::default()\n33\t}\n34\t\n35\tfn all_tools() -> Vec<String> {\n36\t    vec![\n37\t        \"read_file\".into(),\n38\t        \"shell\".into(),\n39\t        \"write_file\".into(),\n40\t        \"search\".into(),\n41\t    ]\n42\t}\n43\t\n44\tfn resolve_ctx(\n45\t    configured: AssistantMode,\n46\t    session: Option<AssistantMode>,\n47\t    policy: CapabilityPolicy,\n48\t) -> AssistantModeContext {\n49\t    AssistantModeContext {\n50\t        session_id: sid(),\n51\t        configured_mode: configured,\n52\t        session_mode: session,\n53\t        policy_enabled: true,\n54\t        available_tools: all_tools(),\n55\t        capability_policy: policy,\n56\t    }\n57\t}\n58\t\n59\tfn route_ctx(\n60\t    current: AssistantMode,\n61\t    raw_input: &str,\n62\t    explicit_mode: Option<AssistantMode>,\n63\t    policy: CapabilityPolicy,\n64\t) -> RouteInputContext {\n65\t    RouteInputContext {\n66\t        session_id: sid(),\n67\t        current_mode: current,\n68\t        policy_enabled: true,\n69\t        capability_policy: policy,\n70\t        raw_input: raw_input.into(),\n71\t        explicit_mode,\n72\t    }\n73\t}\n74\t\n75\t// ── §7.1 Contract tests ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n76\t\n77\t/// AC: mode resolution is deterministic for same inputs.\n78\t///\n79\t/// Given identical inputs, resolve_mode must produce the same effective_mode,\n80\t/// source, and switch_event every time.\n81\t#[test]\n82\tfn contract_mode_resolution_is_deterministic_for_same_inputs() {\n83\t    let service = svc();\n84\t    let ctx = resolve_ctx(\n85\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n86\t        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n87\t        default_policy(),\n88\t    );\n89\t\n90\t    let a = service.resolve_mode(ctx.clone());\n91\t    let b = service.resolve_mode(ctx);\n92\t\n93\t    assert_eq!(\n94\t        a.effective_mode, b.effective_mode,\n95\t        \"effective_mode must be deterministic\"\n96\t    );\n97\t    assert_eq!(a.source, b.source, \"source must be deterministic\");\n98\t    assert_eq!(\n99\t        a.visible_tools, b.visible_tools,\n100\t        \"visible_tools must be deterministic\"\n101\t    );\n102\t    assert!(a.error.is_none());\n103\t    assert!(b.error.is_none());\n104\t}\n105\t\n106\t/// AC: mode resolution determinism holds when session_mode is None.\n107\t#[test]\n108\tfn contract_mode_resolution_deterministic_without_session() {\n109\t    let service = svc();\n110\t    let ctx = resolve_ctx(AssistantMode::KairosChannels, None, default_policy());\n111\t\n112\t    let a = service.resolve_mode(ctx.clone());\n113\t    let b = service.resolve_mode(ctx);\n114\t\n115\t    assert_eq!(a.effective_mode, b.effective_mode);\n116\t    assert_eq!(a.source, b.source);\n117\t    assert_eq!(a.source, ResolvedModeSource::Config);\n118\t}\n119\t\n120\t/// AC: route precedence is deterministic.\n121\t///\n122\t/// SlashCommand and ExplicitOverride sources are resolved consistently.\n123\t#[test]\n124\tfn contract_route_precedence_is_deterministic() {\n125\t    let service = svc();\n126\t    let ctx = route_ctx(\n127\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n128\t        \"/brief summarize\",\n129\t        None,\n130\t        default_policy(),\n131\t    );\n132\t\n133\t    let a = service.route_input(ctx.clone());\n134\t    let b = service.route_input(ctx);\n135\t\n136\t    assert_eq!(a.source, b.source, \"route source must be deterministic\");\n137\t    assert_eq!(a.next_mode, b.next_mode, \"next_mode must be deterministic\");\n138\t    assert_eq!(\n139\t        a.passthrough_input, b.passthrough_input,\n140\t        \"passthrough must be deterministic\"\n141\t    );\n142\t    assert_eq!(a.source, RouteSource::SlashCommand);\n143\t}\n144\t\n145\t/// AC: explicit override takes precedence over slash command when they agree.\n146\t#[test]\n147\tfn contract_explicit_override_precedence_when_aligned() {\n148\t    let service = svc();\n149\t    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n150\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n151\t        \"/brief summarize\",\n152\t        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n153\t        default_policy(),\n154\t    ));\n155\t\n156\t    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n157\t    assert_eq!(decision.source, RouteSource::ExplicitOverride);\n158\t    assert_eq!(decision.next_mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n159\t}\n160\t\n161\t/// AC: PromptComposeFailed returned on invalid compose context.\n162\t///\n163\t/// When no prompt layers are available (all None/empty and mode prompt produces\n164\t/// empty after join), PromptComposeFailed is emitted.\n165\t#[test]\n166\tfn contract_prompt_compose_failed_on_invalid_context() {\n167\t    let service = svc();\n168\t\n169\t    // With all optional prompts None, only ModeDefault layer is added,\n170\t    // so it won't be empty. We need to test the contract error path.\n171\t    // The PromptComposeFailed is only returned when system_prompt is empty,\n172\t    // which can't happen with ModeDefault always present.\n173\t    // However, when policy is disabled, we get DisabledByPolicy instead.\n174\t    // Test with a mode not allowed by capability_policy.\n175\t    let mut policy = default_policy();\n176\t    policy.allow_brief_mode = false;\n177\t\n178\t    let result = service.build_prompt(PromptComposeContext {\n179\t        mode: AssistantMode::KairosBrief,\n180\t        policy_enabled: true,\n181\t        capability_policy: policy,\n182\t        base_prompt: None,\n183\t        mode_prompt_override: None,\n184\t        policy_prompt: None,\n185\t        runtime_prompt: None,\n186\t    });\n187\t\n188\t    assert!(\n189\t        result.error.is_some(),\n190\t        \"should return error for disallowed mode\"\n191\t    );\n192\t    assert!(\n193\t        matches!(\n194\t            result.error.as_ref().unwrap(),\n195\t            KairosError::InvalidModeState\n196\t        ),\n197\t        \"expected InvalidModeState for disallowed brief mode, got {:?}\",\n198\t        result.error\n199\t    );\n200\t}\n201\t\n202\t/// AC: PromptComposeFailed specifically – policy disabled yields empty prompt.\n203\t#[test]\n204\tfn contract_prompt_compose_disabled_by_policy() {\n205\t    let service = svc();\n206\t    let result = service.build_prompt(PromptComposeContext {\n207\t        mode: AssistantMode::Kairos,\n208\t        policy_enabled: false,\n209\t        capability_policy: default_policy(),\n210\t        base_prompt: Some(\"base\".into()),\n211\t        mode_prompt_override: None,\n212\t        policy_prompt: None,\n213\t        runtime_prompt: None,\n214\t    });\n215\t\n216\t    assert!(result.error.is_some());\n217\t    assert!(\n218\t        matches!(\n219\t            result.error.as_ref().unwrap(),\n220\t            KairosError::DisabledByPolicy\n221\t        ),\n222\t        \"expected DisabledByPolicy, got {:?}\",\n223\t        result.error\n224\t    );\n225\t    assert!(\n226\t        result.system_prompt.is_empty(),\n227\t        \"system prompt should be empty when disabled\"\n228\t    );\n229\t}\n230\t\n231\t// ── §7.2 Integration tests ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n232\t\n233\t/// AC: KAIROS mode – all tools visible when no blocked tools.\n234\t#[test]\n235\tfn integration_kairos_mode_all_tools_visible() {\n236\t    let service = svc();\n237\t    let decision = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(AssistantMode::Kairos, None, default_policy()));\n238\t\n239\t    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n240\t    assert_eq!(decision.effective_mode, AssistantMode::Kairos);\n241\t    assert_eq!(decision.visible_tools, all_tools());\n242\t}\n243\t\n244\t/// AC: KAIROS_BRIEF mode – brief_blocked_tools are filtered out.\n245\t#[test]\n246\tfn integration_brief_mode_filters_brief_blocked_tools() {\n247\t    let service = svc();\n248\t    let mut policy = default_policy();\n249\t    policy.brief_blocked_tools = vec![\"shell\".into(), \"write_file\".into()];\n250\t\n251\t    let decision = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n252\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n253\t        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n254\t        policy,\n255\t    ));\n256\t\n257\t    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n258\t    assert_eq!(decision.effective_mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n259\t    assert!(\n260\t        !decision.visible_tools.contains(&\"shell\".into()),\n261\t        \"shell should be blocked in brief mode\"\n262\t    );\n263\t    assert!(\n264\t        !decision.visible_tools.contains(&\"write_file\".into()),\n265\t        \"write_file should be blocked in brief mode\"\n266\t    );\n267\t    assert!(\n268\t        decision.visible_tools.contains(&\"read_file\".into()),\n269\t        \"read_file should remain visible\"\n270\t    );\n271\t    assert!(\n272\t        decision.visible_tools.contains(&\"search\".into()),\n273\t        \"search should remain visible\"\n274\t    );\n275\t}\n276\t\n277\t/// AC: KAIROS_CHANNELS mode – globally blocked tools filtered.\n278\t#[test]\n279\tfn integration_channels_mode_respects_blocked_tools() {\n280\t    let service = svc();\n281\t    let mut policy = default_policy();\n282\t    policy.blocked_tools = vec![\"shell\".into()];\n283\t\n284\t    let decision = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n285\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n286\t        Some(AssistantMode::KairosChannels),\n287\t        policy,\n288\t    ));\n289\t\n290\t    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n291\t    assert_eq!(decision.effective_mode, AssistantMode::KairosChannels);\n292\t    assert!(\n293\t        !decision.visible_tools.contains(&\"shell\".into()),\n294\t        \"shell should be globally blocked\"\n295\t    );\n296\t    assert_eq!(decision.visible_tools.len(), 3);\n297\t}\n298\t\n299\t/// AC: KAIROS/BRIEF combination – both blocked_tools and brief_blocked_tools apply.\n300\t#[test]\n301\tfn integration_brief_mode_applies_both_block_lists() {\n302\t    let service = svc();\n303\t    let mut policy = default_policy();\n304\t    policy.blocked_tools = vec![\"shell\".into()];\n305\t    policy.brief_blocked_tools = vec![\"write_file\".into()];\n306\t\n307\t    let decision = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n308\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n309\t        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n310\t        policy,\n311\t    ));\n312\t\n313\t    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n314\t    assert_eq!(\n315\t        decision.visible_tools,\n316\t        vec![\"read_file\".to_string(), \"search\".to_string()],\n317\t        \"only read_file and search should survive both block lists\"\n318\t    );\n319\t}\n320\t\n321\t/// AC: slash routing /brief produces correct mode switch.\n322\t#[test]\n323\tfn integration_slash_brief_routing_matches_semantics() {\n324\t    let service = svc();\n325\t    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n326\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n327\t        \"/brief summarize the code\",\n328\t        None,\n329\t        default_policy(),\n330\t    ));\n331\t\n332\t    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n333\t    assert_eq!(decision.source, RouteSource::SlashCommand);\n334\t    assert_eq!(decision.next_mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n335\t    assert!(decision.command_consumed);\n336\t    assert_eq!(decision.passthrough_input, \"summarize the code\");\n337\t    assert!(\n338\t        matches!(\n339\t            decision.switch_event,\n340\t            Some(DomainEvent::AssistantModeSwitched {\n341\t                from_mode: AssistantMode::Kairos,\n342\t                to_mode: AssistantMode::KairosBrief,\n343\t                trigger: ModeSwitchTrigger::SlashCommand,\n344\t                ..\n345\t            })\n346\t        ),\n347\t        \"expected mode switch event, got {:?}\",\n348\t        decision.switch_event\n349\t    );\n350\t}\n351\t\n352\t/// AC: slash routing /channels produces correct mode switch.\n353\t#[test]\n354\tfn integration_slash_channels_routing_matches_semantics() {\n355\t    let service = svc();\n356\t    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n357\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n358\t        \"/channels coordinate agents\",\n359\t        None,\n360\t        default_policy(),\n361\t    ));\n362\t\n363\t    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n364\t    assert_eq!(decision.source, RouteSource::SlashCommand);\n365\t    assert_eq!(decision.next_mode, AssistantMode::KairosChannels);\n366\t    assert!(decision.command_consumed);\n367\t    assert_eq!(decision.passthrough_input, \"coordinate agents\");\n368\t}\n369\t\n370\t/// AC: slash routing /kairos from brief mode switches back.\n371\t#[test]\n372\tfn integration_slash_kairos_routing_from_brief() {\n373\t    let service = svc();\n374\t    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n375\t        AssistantMode::KairosBrief,\n376\t        \"/kairos explain in detail\",\n377\t        None,\n378\t        default_policy(),\n379\t    ));\n380\t\n381\t    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n382\t    assert_eq!(decision.next_mode, AssistantMode::Kairos);\n383\t    assert!(decision.command_consumed);\n384\t    assert_eq!(decision.passthrough_input, \"explain in detail\");\n385\t}\n386\t\n387\t/// AC: non-slash input is passed through without mode change.\n388\t#[test]\n389\tfn integration_non_slash_input_passthrough() {\n390\t    let service = svc();\n391\t    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n392\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n393\t        \"just a normal message\",\n394\t        None,\n395\t        default_policy(),\n396\t    ));\n397\t\n398\t    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n399\t    assert_eq!(decision.source, RouteSource::Noop);\n400\t    assert_eq!(decision.next_mode, AssistantMode::Kairos);\n401\t    assert!(!decision.command_consumed);\n402\t    assert_eq!(decision.passthrough_input, \"just a normal message\");\n403\t    assert!(decision.switch_event.is_none());\n404\t}\n405\t\n406\t/// AC: RouteConflict handled gracefully when multiple routes match.\n407\t///\n408\t/// When explicit_mode disagrees with slash command, RouteConflict is emitted\n409\t/// and current mode is preserved.\n410\t#[test]\n411\tfn integration_route_conflict_handled_gracefully() {\n412\t    let service = svc();\n413\t    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n414\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n415\t        \"/brief summarize\",\n416\t        Some(AssistantMode::KairosChannels),\n417\t        default_policy(),\n418\t    ));\n419\t\n420\t    assert_eq!(\n421\t        decision.source,\n422\t        RouteSource::Conflict,\n423\t        \"conflicting routes must produce Conflict source\"\n424\t    );\n425\t    assert!(\n426\t        matches!(decision.error.as_ref().unwrap(), KairosError::RouteConflict),\n427\t        \"expected RouteConflict error, got {:?}\",\n428\t        decision.error\n429\t    );\n430\t    assert_eq!(\n431\t        decision.next_mode,\n432\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n433\t        \"current mode preserved on conflict\"\n434\t    );\n435\t    assert!(\n436\t        !decision.command_consumed,\n437\t        \"command not consumed on conflict\"\n438\t    );\n439\t    assert!(\n440\t        decision.switch_event.is_none(),\n441\t        \"no switch event on conflict\"\n442\t    );\n443\t}\n444\t\n445\t/// AC: RouteConflict – agreeing explicit and slash is not a conflict.\n446\t#[test]\n447\tfn integration_route_no_conflict_when_modes_agree() {\n448\t    let service = svc();\n449\t    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n450\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n451\t        \"/channels do work\",\n452\t        Some(AssistantMode::KairosChannels),\n453\t        default_policy(),\n454\t    ));\n455\t\n456\t    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n457\t    assert_eq!(decision.source, RouteSource::ExplicitOverride);\n458\t    assert_eq!(decision.next_mode, AssistantMode::KairosChannels);\n459\t}\n460\t\n461\t// ── §7.3 CLI behaviour tests ────────────────────────────────────────────\n462\t\n463\t/// AC: assistant-mode entry behaviour matches current semantics.\n464\t///\n465\t/// When session_mode is set, it overrides configured_mode.\n466\t/// When session_mode is None, configured_mode is used.\n467\t#[test]\n468\tfn cli_assistant_mode_entry_session_overrides_config() {\n469\t    let service = svc();\n470\t\n471\t    let with_session = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n472\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n473\t        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n474\t        default_policy(),\n475\t    ));\n476\t    assert_eq!(with_session.effective_mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n477\t    assert_eq!(with_session.source, ResolvedModeSource::Session);\n478\t\n479\t    let without_session =\n480\t        service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(AssistantMode::Kairos, None, default_policy()));\n481\t    assert_eq!(without_session.effective_mode, AssistantMode::Kairos);\n482\t    assert_eq!(without_session.source, ResolvedModeSource::Config);\n483\t}\n484\t\n485\t/// AC: assistant-mode entry emits switch event only when modes differ.\n486\t#[test]\n487\tfn cli_assistant_mode_entry_switch_event_only_on_change() {\n488\t    let service = svc();\n489\t\n490\t    // Different modes → event emitted.\n491\t    let switched = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n492\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n493\t        Some(AssistantMode::KairosChannels),\n494\t        default_policy(),\n495\t    ));\n496\t    assert!(\n497\t        switched.switch_event.is_some(),\n498\t        \"switch event expected when modes differ\"\n499\t    );\n500\t\n501\t    // Same mode → no event.\n502\t    let same = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n503\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n504\t        Some(AssistantMode::Kairos),\n505\t        default_policy(),\n506\t    ));\n507\t    assert!(\n508\t        same.switch_event.is_none(),\n509\t        \"no switch event when mode stays the same\"\n510\t    );\n511\t}\n512\t\n513\t/// AC: DisabledByPolicy surfaced as actionable message.\n514\t///\n515\t/// When policy_enabled is false, resolve_mode returns DisabledByPolicy\n516\t/// with the configured mode preserved.\n517\t#[test]\n518\tfn cli_disabled_by_policy_surfaced_as_actionable_message() {\n519\t    let service = svc();\n520\t    let decision = service.resolve_mode(AssistantModeContext {\n521\t        session_id: sid(),\n522\t        configured_mode: AssistantMode::Kairos,\n523\t        session_mode: Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n524\t        policy_enabled: false,\n525\t        available_tools: all_tools(),\n526\t        capability_policy: default_policy(),\n527\t    });\n528\t\n529\t    assert!(\n530\t        matches!(\n531\t            decision.error.as_ref().unwrap(),\n532\t            KairosError::DisabledByPolicy\n533\t        ),\n534\t        \"expected DisabledByPolicy, got {:?}\",\n535\t        decision.error\n536\t    );\n537\t    assert_eq!(\n538\t        decision.effective_mode,\n539\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n540\t        \"configured mode preserved when disabled\"\n541\t    );\n542\t    assert_eq!(\n543\t        decision.source,\n544\t        ResolvedModeSource::Config,\n545\t        \"source is Config when disabled by policy\"\n546\t    );\n547\t\n548\t    // Verify the error message is actionable (Display impl).\n549\t    let msg = format!(\"{}\", decision.error.unwrap());\n550\t    assert!(\n551\t        msg.contains(\"disabled by policy\"),\n552\t        \"error message should be actionable: '{msg}'\"\n553\t    );\n554\t}\n555\t\n556\t/// AC: DisabledByPolicy on capability_policy.allow_assistant_modes = false.\n557\t#[test]\n558\tfn cli_disabled_by_capability_policy() {\n559\t    let service = svc();\n560\t    let mut policy = default_policy();\n561\t    policy.allow_assistant_modes = false;\n562\t\n563\t    let decision = service.resolve_mode(AssistantModeContext {\n564\t        session_id: sid(),\n565\t        configured_mode: AssistantMode::Kairos,\n566\t        session_mode: Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n567\t        policy_enabled: true,\n568\t        available_tools: all_tools(),\n569\t        capability_policy: policy,\n570\t    });\n571\t\n572\t    assert!(matches!(\n573\t        decision.error.as_ref().unwrap(),\n574\t        KairosError::DisabledByPolicy\n575\t    ));\n576\t}\n577\t\n578\t/// AC: mode switch via /brief command works end-to-end.\n579\t///\n580\t/// Starting from Kairos mode, /brief routes correctly, produces a switch event,\n581\t/// and the resulting mode's prompt composition succeeds.\n582\t#[test]\n583\tfn cli_mode_switch_via_brief_end_to_end() {\n584\t    let service = svc();\n585\t\n586\t    // Step 1: Route the /brief command.\n587\t    let route = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n588\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n589\t        \"/brief be concise\",\n590\t        None,\n591\t        default_policy(),\n592\t    ));\n593\t    assert!(route.error.is_none());\n594\t    assert_eq!(route.next_mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n595\t    assert!(route.command_consumed);\n596\t    assert_eq!(route.passthrough_input, \"be concise\");\n597\t    assert!(\n598\t        matches!(\n599\t            route.switch_event,\n600\t            Some(DomainEvent::AssistantModeSwitched {\n601\t                from_mode: AssistantMode::Kairos,\n602\t                to_mode: AssistantMode::KairosBrief,\n603\t                trigger: ModeSwitchTrigger::SlashCommand,\n604\t                ..\n605\t            })\n606\t        ),\n607\t        \"switch event with SlashCommand trigger expected\"\n608\t    );\n609\t\n610\t    // Step 2: Build prompt in the new mode.\n611\t    let prompt = service.build_prompt(PromptComposeContext {\n612\t        mode: route.next_mode,\n613\t        policy_enabled: true,\n614\t        capability_policy: default_policy(),\n615\t        base_prompt: Some(\"system base prompt\".into()),\n616\t        mode_prompt_override: None,\n617\t        policy_prompt: None,\n618\t        runtime_prompt: None,\n619\t    });\n620\t    assert!(prompt.error.is_none());\n621\t    assert!(\n622\t        prompt\n623\t            .system_prompt\n624\t            .contains(\"KAIROS BRIEF mode. Keep responses concise\"),\n625\t        \"brief mode prompt should be in composed output\"\n626\t    );\n627\t    assert_eq!(\n628\t        prompt.precedence,\n629\t        vec![\n630\t            PromptPrecedenceLayer::Base,\n631\t            PromptPrecedenceLayer::ModeDefault,\n632\t        ]\n633\t    );\n634\t    assert_eq!(prompt.telemetry_tags.mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n635\t    assert!(prompt.telemetry_tags.brief_active);\n636\t    assert!(!prompt.telemetry_tags.channels_active);\n637\t\n638\t    // Step 3: Resolve mode with the switched state persisted in session.\n639\t    let resolved = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n640\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n641\t        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n642\t        default_policy(),\n643\t    ));\n644\t    assert!(resolved.error.is_none());\n645\t    assert_eq!(resolved.effective_mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n646\t    assert_eq!(resolved.source, ResolvedModeSource::Session);\n647\t}\n648\t\n649\t/// AC: DisabledByPolicy on route_input returns noop with error.\n650\t#[test]\n651\tfn cli_route_disabled_by_policy_returns_noop() {\n652\t    let service = svc();\n653\t    let decision = service.route_input(RouteInputContext {\n654\t        session_id: sid(),\n655\t        current_mode: AssistantMode::Kairos,\n656\t        policy_enabled: false,\n657\t        capability_policy: default_policy(),\n658\t        raw_input: \"/brief test\".into(),\n659\t        explicit_mode: None,\n660\t    });\n661\t\n662\t    assert_eq!(decision.source, RouteSource::Noop);\n663\t    assert!(!decision.command_consumed);\n664\t    assert!(matches!(\n665\t        decision.error.as_ref().unwrap(),\n666\t        KairosError::DisabledByPolicy\n667\t    ));\n668\t}\n669\t\n670\t/// AC: telemetry tags reflect correct mode state.\n671\t#[test]\n672\tfn cli_telemetry_tags_reflect_mode_state() {\n673\t    let service = svc();\n674\t\n675\t    let kairos = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(AssistantMode::Kairos, None, default_policy()));\n676\t    assert!(kairos.telemetry_tags.kairos_active);\n677\t    assert!(!kairos.telemetry_tags.brief_active);\n678\t    assert!(!kairos.telemetry_tags.channels_active);\n679\t\n680\t    let brief = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n681\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n682\t        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n683\t        default_policy(),\n684\t    ));\n685\t    assert!(brief.telemetry_tags.kairos_active);\n686\t    assert!(brief.telemetry_tags.brief_active);\n687\t    assert!(!brief.telemetry_tags.channels_active);\n688\t\n689\t    let channels = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n690\t        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n691\t        Some(AssistantMode::KairosChannels),\n692\t        default_policy(),\n693\t    ));\n694\t    assert!(channels.telemetry_tags.kairos_active);\n695\t    assert!(!channels.telemetry_tags.brief_active);\n696\t    assert!(channels.telemetry_tags.channels_active);\n697\t}\n698\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f364ad52-4738-45a7-8cb7-9f4703f698a1","uuid":"52a66aa0-7eb7-4a17-957e-c44db2b46d88","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:47:41.572Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/kairos_acceptance_tests.rs","content":"/// KAIROS acceptance tests (US-040)\n///\n/// Covers all scenarios from kairos-contract.md §7 Acceptance Matrix:\n///   §7.1 Contract tests  – mode resolution determinism, route precedence, PromptComposeFailed\n///   §7.2 Integration tests – KAIROS/BRIEF/CHANNELS tool visibility, slash routing, RouteConflict\n///   §7.3 CLI behaviour tests – assistant-mode entry, DisabledByPolicy message, /brief switch\nuse crate::{\n    assistant_mode_service::DefaultAssistantModeService,\n    spec_contracts::{\n        AssistantModeContext, AssistantModeService, CapabilityPolicy, KairosError,\n        PromptComposeContext, PromptPrecedenceLayer, ResolvedModeSource, RouteDecision,\n        RouteInputContext, RouteSource,\n    },\n};\nuse ccode_domain::{\n    assistant_mode::{AssistantMode, ModeSwitchTrigger},\n    event::DomainEvent,\n    session::SessionId,\n};\n\n// ── helpers ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfn sid() -> SessionId {\n    SessionId(\"kairos-test-sess\".into())\n}\n\nfn svc() -> DefaultAssistantModeService {\n    DefaultAssistantModeService\n}\n\nfn default_policy() -> CapabilityPolicy {\n    CapabilityPolicy::default()\n}\n\nfn all_tools() -> Vec<String> {\n    vec![\n        \"read_file\".into(),\n        \"shell\".into(),\n        \"write_file\".into(),\n        \"search\".into(),\n    ]\n}\n\nfn resolve_ctx(\n    configured: AssistantMode,\n    session: Option<AssistantMode>,\n    policy: CapabilityPolicy,\n) -> AssistantModeContext {\n    AssistantModeContext {\n        session_id: sid(),\n        configured_mode: configured,\n        session_mode: session,\n        policy_enabled: true,\n        available_tools: all_tools(),\n        capability_policy: policy,\n    }\n}\n\nfn route_ctx(\n    current: AssistantMode,\n    raw_input: &str,\n    explicit_mode: Option<AssistantMode>,\n    policy: CapabilityPolicy,\n) -> RouteInputContext {\n    RouteInputContext {\n        session_id: sid(),\n        current_mode: current,\n        policy_enabled: true,\n        capability_policy: policy,\n        raw_input: raw_input.into(),\n        explicit_mode,\n    }\n}\n\n// ── §7.1 Contract tests ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/// AC: mode resolution is deterministic for same inputs.\n///\n/// Given identical inputs, resolve_mode must produce the same effective_mode,\n/// source, and switch_event every time.\n#[test]\nfn contract_mode_resolution_is_deterministic_for_same_inputs() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let ctx = resolve_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n        default_policy(),\n    );\n\n    let a = service.resolve_mode(ctx.clone());\n    let b = service.resolve_mode(ctx);\n\n    assert_eq!(\n        a.effective_mode, b.effective_mode,\n        \"effective_mode must be deterministic\"\n    );\n    assert_eq!(a.source, b.source, \"source must be deterministic\");\n    assert_eq!(\n        a.visible_tools, b.visible_tools,\n        \"visible_tools must be deterministic\"\n    );\n    assert!(a.error.is_none());\n    assert!(b.error.is_none());\n}\n\n/// AC: mode resolution determinism holds when session_mode is None.\n#[test]\nfn contract_mode_resolution_deterministic_without_session() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let ctx = resolve_ctx(AssistantMode::KairosChannels, None, default_policy());\n\n    let a = service.resolve_mode(ctx.clone());\n    let b = service.resolve_mode(ctx);\n\n    assert_eq!(a.effective_mode, b.effective_mode);\n    assert_eq!(a.source, b.source);\n    assert_eq!(a.source, ResolvedModeSource::Config);\n}\n\n/// AC: route precedence is deterministic.\n///\n/// SlashCommand and ExplicitOverride sources are resolved consistently.\n#[test]\nfn contract_route_precedence_is_deterministic() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let ctx = route_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        \"/brief summarize\",\n        None,\n        default_policy(),\n    );\n\n    let a = service.route_input(ctx.clone());\n    let b = service.route_input(ctx);\n\n    assert_eq!(a.source, b.source, \"route source must be deterministic\");\n    assert_eq!(a.next_mode, b.next_mode, \"next_mode must be deterministic\");\n    assert_eq!(\n        a.passthrough_input, b.passthrough_input,\n        \"passthrough must be deterministic\"\n    );\n    assert_eq!(a.source, RouteSource::SlashCommand);\n}\n\n/// AC: explicit override takes precedence over slash command when they agree.\n#[test]\nfn contract_explicit_override_precedence_when_aligned() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        \"/brief summarize\",\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n\n    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n    assert_eq!(decision.source, RouteSource::ExplicitOverride);\n    assert_eq!(decision.next_mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n}\n\n/// AC: PromptComposeFailed returned on invalid compose context.\n///\n/// When no prompt layers are available (all None/empty and mode prompt produces\n/// empty after join), PromptComposeFailed is emitted.\n#[test]\nfn contract_prompt_compose_failed_on_invalid_context() {\n    let service = svc();\n\n    // With all optional prompts None, only ModeDefault layer is added,\n    // so it won't be empty. We need to test the contract error path.\n    // The PromptComposeFailed is only returned when system_prompt is empty,\n    // which can't happen with ModeDefault always present.\n    // However, when policy is disabled, we get DisabledByPolicy instead.\n    // Test with a mode not allowed by capability_policy.\n    let mut policy = default_policy();\n    policy.allow_brief_mode = false;\n\n    let result = service.build_prompt(PromptComposeContext {\n        mode: AssistantMode::KairosBrief,\n        policy_enabled: true,\n        capability_policy: policy,\n        base_prompt: None,\n        mode_prompt_override: None,\n        policy_prompt: None,\n        runtime_prompt: None,\n    });\n\n    assert!(\n        result.error.is_some(),\n        \"should return error for disallowed mode\"\n    );\n    assert!(\n        matches!(\n            result.error.as_ref().unwrap(),\n            KairosError::InvalidModeState\n        ),\n        \"expected InvalidModeState for disallowed brief mode, got {:?}\",\n        result.error\n    );\n}\n\n/// AC: PromptComposeFailed specifically – policy disabled yields empty prompt.\n#[test]\nfn contract_prompt_compose_disabled_by_policy() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let result = service.build_prompt(PromptComposeContext {\n        mode: AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        policy_enabled: false,\n        capability_policy: default_policy(),\n        base_prompt: Some(\"base\".into()),\n        mode_prompt_override: None,\n        policy_prompt: None,\n        runtime_prompt: None,\n    });\n\n    assert!(result.error.is_some());\n    assert!(\n        matches!(\n            result.error.as_ref().unwrap(),\n            KairosError::DisabledByPolicy\n        ),\n        \"expected DisabledByPolicy, got {:?}\",\n        result.error\n    );\n    assert!(\n        result.system_prompt.is_empty(),\n        \"system prompt should be empty when disabled\"\n    );\n}\n\n// ── §7.2 Integration tests ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/// AC: KAIROS mode – all tools visible when no blocked tools.\n#[test]\nfn integration_kairos_mode_all_tools_visible() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let decision = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(AssistantMode::Kairos, None, default_policy()));\n\n    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n    assert_eq!(decision.effective_mode, AssistantMode::Kairos);\n    assert_eq!(decision.visible_tools, all_tools());\n}\n\n/// AC: KAIROS_BRIEF mode – brief_blocked_tools are filtered out.\n#[test]\nfn integration_brief_mode_filters_brief_blocked_tools() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let mut policy = default_policy();\n    policy.brief_blocked_tools = vec![\"shell\".into(), \"write_file\".into()];\n\n    let decision = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n        policy,\n    ));\n\n    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n    assert_eq!(decision.effective_mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n    assert!(\n        !decision.visible_tools.contains(&\"shell\".into()),\n        \"shell should be blocked in brief mode\"\n    );\n    assert!(\n        !decision.visible_tools.contains(&\"write_file\".into()),\n        \"write_file should be blocked in brief mode\"\n    );\n    assert!(\n        decision.visible_tools.contains(&\"read_file\".into()),\n        \"read_file should remain visible\"\n    );\n    assert!(\n        decision.visible_tools.contains(&\"search\".into()),\n        \"search should remain visible\"\n    );\n}\n\n/// AC: KAIROS_CHANNELS mode – globally blocked tools filtered.\n#[test]\nfn integration_channels_mode_respects_blocked_tools() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let mut policy = default_policy();\n    policy.blocked_tools = vec![\"shell\".into()];\n\n    let decision = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosChannels),\n        policy,\n    ));\n\n    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n    assert_eq!(decision.effective_mode, AssistantMode::KairosChannels);\n    assert!(\n        !decision.visible_tools.contains(&\"shell\".into()),\n        \"shell should be globally blocked\"\n    );\n    assert_eq!(decision.visible_tools.len(), 3);\n}\n\n/// AC: KAIROS/BRIEF combination – both blocked_tools and brief_blocked_tools apply.\n#[test]\nfn integration_brief_mode_applies_both_block_lists() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let mut policy = default_policy();\n    policy.blocked_tools = vec![\"shell\".into()];\n    policy.brief_blocked_tools = vec![\"write_file\".into()];\n\n    let decision = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n        policy,\n    ));\n\n    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n    assert_eq!(\n        decision.visible_tools,\n        vec![\"read_file\".to_string(), \"search\".to_string()],\n        \"only read_file and search should survive both block lists\"\n    );\n}\n\n/// AC: slash routing /brief produces correct mode switch.\n#[test]\nfn integration_slash_brief_routing_matches_semantics() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        \"/brief summarize the code\",\n        None,\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n\n    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n    assert_eq!(decision.source, RouteSource::SlashCommand);\n    assert_eq!(decision.next_mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n    assert!(decision.command_consumed);\n    assert_eq!(decision.passthrough_input, \"summarize the code\");\n    assert!(\n        matches!(\n            decision.switch_event,\n            Some(DomainEvent::AssistantModeSwitched {\n                from_mode: AssistantMode::Kairos,\n                to_mode: AssistantMode::KairosBrief,\n                trigger: ModeSwitchTrigger::SlashCommand,\n                ..\n            })\n        ),\n        \"expected mode switch event, got {:?}\",\n        decision.switch_event\n    );\n}\n\n/// AC: slash routing /channels produces correct mode switch.\n#[test]\nfn integration_slash_channels_routing_matches_semantics() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        \"/channels coordinate agents\",\n        None,\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n\n    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n    assert_eq!(decision.source, RouteSource::SlashCommand);\n    assert_eq!(decision.next_mode, AssistantMode::KairosChannels);\n    assert!(decision.command_consumed);\n    assert_eq!(decision.passthrough_input, \"coordinate agents\");\n}\n\n/// AC: slash routing /kairos from brief mode switches back.\n#[test]\nfn integration_slash_kairos_routing_from_brief() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::KairosBrief,\n        \"/kairos explain in detail\",\n        None,\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n\n    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n    assert_eq!(decision.next_mode, AssistantMode::Kairos);\n    assert!(decision.command_consumed);\n    assert_eq!(decision.passthrough_input, \"explain in detail\");\n}\n\n/// AC: non-slash input is passed through without mode change.\n#[test]\nfn integration_non_slash_input_passthrough() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        \"just a normal message\",\n        None,\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n\n    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n    assert_eq!(decision.source, RouteSource::Noop);\n    assert_eq!(decision.next_mode, AssistantMode::Kairos);\n    assert!(!decision.command_consumed);\n    assert_eq!(decision.passthrough_input, \"just a normal message\");\n    assert!(decision.switch_event.is_none());\n}\n\n/// AC: RouteConflict handled gracefully when multiple routes match.\n///\n/// When explicit_mode disagrees with slash command, RouteConflict is emitted\n/// and current mode is preserved.\n#[test]\nfn integration_route_conflict_handled_gracefully() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        \"/brief summarize\",\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosChannels),\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n\n    assert_eq!(\n        decision.source,\n        RouteSource::Conflict,\n        \"conflicting routes must produce Conflict source\"\n    );\n    assert!(\n        matches!(decision.error.as_ref().unwrap(), KairosError::RouteConflict),\n        \"expected RouteConflict error, got {:?}\",\n        decision.error\n    );\n    assert_eq!(\n        decision.next_mode,\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        \"current mode preserved on conflict\"\n    );\n    assert!(\n        !decision.command_consumed,\n        \"command not consumed on conflict\"\n    );\n    assert!(\n        decision.switch_event.is_none(),\n        \"no switch event on conflict\"\n    );\n}\n\n/// AC: RouteConflict – agreeing explicit and slash is not a conflict.\n#[test]\nfn integration_route_no_conflict_when_modes_agree() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let decision = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        \"/channels do work\",\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosChannels),\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n\n    assert!(decision.error.is_none());\n    assert_eq!(decision.source, RouteSource::ExplicitOverride);\n    assert_eq!(decision.next_mode, AssistantMode::KairosChannels);\n}\n\n// ── §7.3 CLI behaviour tests ────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/// AC: assistant-mode entry behaviour matches current semantics.\n///\n/// When session_mode is set, it overrides configured_mode.\n/// When session_mode is None, configured_mode is used.\n#[test]\nfn cli_assistant_mode_entry_session_overrides_config() {\n    let service = svc();\n\n    let with_session = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n    assert_eq!(with_session.effective_mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n    assert_eq!(with_session.source, ResolvedModeSource::Session);\n\n    let without_session =\n        service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(AssistantMode::Kairos, None, default_policy()));\n    assert_eq!(without_session.effective_mode, AssistantMode::Kairos);\n    assert_eq!(without_session.source, ResolvedModeSource::Config);\n}\n\n/// AC: assistant-mode entry emits switch event only when modes differ.\n#[test]\nfn cli_assistant_mode_entry_switch_event_only_on_change() {\n    let service = svc();\n\n    // Different modes → event emitted.\n    let switched = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosChannels),\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n    assert!(\n        switched.switch_event.is_some(),\n        \"switch event expected when modes differ\"\n    );\n\n    // Same mode → no event.\n    let same = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        Some(AssistantMode::Kairos),\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n    assert!(\n        same.switch_event.is_none(),\n        \"no switch event when mode stays the same\"\n    );\n}\n\n/// AC: DisabledByPolicy surfaced as actionable message.\n///\n/// When policy_enabled is false, resolve_mode returns DisabledByPolicy\n/// with the configured mode preserved.\n#[test]\nfn cli_disabled_by_policy_surfaced_as_actionable_message() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let decision = service.resolve_mode(AssistantModeContext {\n        session_id: sid(),\n        configured_mode: AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        session_mode: Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n        policy_enabled: false,\n        available_tools: all_tools(),\n        capability_policy: default_policy(),\n    });\n\n    assert!(\n        matches!(\n            decision.error.as_ref().unwrap(),\n            KairosError::DisabledByPolicy\n        ),\n        \"expected DisabledByPolicy, got {:?}\",\n        decision.error\n    );\n    assert_eq!(\n        decision.effective_mode,\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        \"configured mode preserved when disabled\"\n    );\n    assert_eq!(\n        decision.source,\n        ResolvedModeSource::Config,\n        \"source is Config when disabled by policy\"\n    );\n\n    // Verify the error message is actionable (Display impl).\n    let msg = format!(\"{}\", decision.error.unwrap());\n    assert!(\n        msg.contains(\"disabled by policy\"),\n        \"error message should be actionable: '{msg}'\"\n    );\n}\n\n/// AC: DisabledByPolicy on capability_policy.allow_assistant_modes = false.\n#[test]\nfn cli_disabled_by_capability_policy() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let mut policy = default_policy();\n    policy.allow_assistant_modes = false;\n\n    let decision = service.resolve_mode(AssistantModeContext {\n        session_id: sid(),\n        configured_mode: AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        session_mode: Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n        policy_enabled: true,\n        available_tools: all_tools(),\n        capability_policy: policy,\n    });\n\n    assert!(matches!(\n        decision.error.as_ref().unwrap(),\n        KairosError::DisabledByPolicy\n    ));\n}\n\n/// AC: mode switch via /brief command works end-to-end.\n///\n/// Starting from Kairos mode, /brief routes correctly, produces a switch event,\n/// and the resulting mode's prompt composition succeeds.\n#[test]\nfn cli_mode_switch_via_brief_end_to_end() {\n    let service = svc();\n\n    // Step 1: Route the /brief command.\n    let route = service.route_input(route_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        \"/brief be concise\",\n        None,\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n    assert!(route.error.is_none());\n    assert_eq!(route.next_mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n    assert!(route.command_consumed);\n    assert_eq!(route.passthrough_input, \"be concise\");\n    assert!(\n        matches!(\n            route.switch_event,\n            Some(DomainEvent::AssistantModeSwitched {\n                from_mode: AssistantMode::Kairos,\n                to_mode: AssistantMode::KairosBrief,\n                trigger: ModeSwitchTrigger::SlashCommand,\n                ..\n            })\n        ),\n        \"switch event with SlashCommand trigger expected\"\n    );\n\n    // Step 2: Build prompt in the new mode.\n    let prompt = service.build_prompt(PromptComposeContext {\n        mode: route.next_mode,\n        policy_enabled: true,\n        capability_policy: default_policy(),\n        base_prompt: Some(\"system base prompt\".into()),\n        mode_prompt_override: None,\n        policy_prompt: None,\n        runtime_prompt: None,\n    });\n    assert!(prompt.error.is_none());\n    assert!(\n        prompt\n            .system_prompt\n            .contains(\"KAIROS BRIEF mode. Keep responses concise\"),\n        \"brief mode prompt should be in composed output\"\n    );\n    assert_eq!(\n        prompt.precedence,\n        vec![\n            PromptPrecedenceLayer::Base,\n            PromptPrecedenceLayer::ModeDefault,\n        ]\n    );\n    assert_eq!(prompt.telemetry_tags.mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n    assert!(prompt.telemetry_tags.brief_active);\n    assert!(!prompt.telemetry_tags.channels_active);\n\n    // Step 3: Resolve mode with the switched state persisted in session.\n    let resolved = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n    assert!(resolved.error.is_none());\n    assert_eq!(resolved.effective_mode, AssistantMode::KairosBrief);\n    assert_eq!(resolved.source, ResolvedModeSource::Session);\n}\n\n/// AC: DisabledByPolicy on route_input returns noop with error.\n#[test]\nfn cli_route_disabled_by_policy_returns_noop() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let decision = service.route_input(RouteInputContext {\n        session_id: sid(),\n        current_mode: AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        policy_enabled: false,\n        capability_policy: default_policy(),\n        raw_input: \"/brief test\".into(),\n        explicit_mode: None,\n    });\n\n    assert_eq!(decision.source, RouteSource::Noop);\n    assert!(!decision.command_consumed);\n    assert!(matches!(\n        decision.error.as_ref().unwrap(),\n        KairosError::DisabledByPolicy\n    ));\n}\n\n/// AC: telemetry tags reflect correct mode state.\n#[test]\nfn cli_telemetry_tags_reflect_mode_state() {\n    let service = svc();\n\n    let kairos = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(AssistantMode::Kairos, None, default_policy()));\n    assert!(kairos.telemetry_tags.kairos_active);\n    assert!(!kairos.telemetry_tags.brief_active);\n    assert!(!kairos.telemetry_tags.channels_active);\n\n    let brief = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n    assert!(brief.telemetry_tags.kairos_active);\n    assert!(brief.telemetry_tags.brief_active);\n    assert!(!brief.telemetry_tags.channels_active);\n\n    let channels = service.resolve_mode(resolve_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosChannels),\n        default_policy(),\n    ));\n    assert!(channels.telemetry_tags.kairos_active);\n    assert!(!channels.telemetry_tags.brief_active);\n    assert!(channels.telemetry_tags.channels_active);\n}\n","numLines":698,"startLine":1,"totalLines":698}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EnvwCAwGgtoRVpwRDSyWjE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The acceptance tests in the application crate follow a specific pattern - they test against the spec_contracts types and service traits. However, for agent triggers, the implementations are in the platform crate where unit tests already exist.\n\nThe acceptance test for agent triggers needs to go in `crates/application/src/agent_triggers_acceptance_tests.rs` and be registered in `crates/application/src/lib.rs`.\n\nLooking at the acceptance matrix from the contract:\n\n### Contract tests\n1. Durable + teammate returns `DurableNotAllowedForTeammate`\n\n\n2. Invalid cron returns `InvalidCron`\n3. Owner mismatch delete returns `OwnershipViolation`\n\n### Integration tests\n1. Session-only task survives runtime tick but not process restart\n2. Durable task reloads from store on restart\n3. Remote dispatch with gate off returns `GateDisabled`\n\n### CLI behavior tests\n1. List shows scope and owner consistently\n2. Delete reports deterministic reason on ownership error\n3. Remote trigger failure prints non-leaky error class\n\nI need to structure the acceptance tests using the spec_contracts types and pull in the platform crate implementations, then figure out what's available to import in the application crate's test module.\n\nActually, I'm noticing the kairos acceptance test only imports from the application crate itself, while the trigger tests pull from the platform crate with things like LocalTriggerSchedulerService. Let me check what dependencies the application crate declares in its Cargo.toml.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13883,"cache_read_input_tokens":24019,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":13883,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f364ad52-4738-45a7-8cb7-9f4703f698a1","uuid":"c9378c61-df01-4303-8797-16c08683b1cc"}
